	"\n" +
	"## Idempotent Operations\n" +
	"\n" +
	"The CLI supports idempotent operations for state-changing commands.\n" +
	"\n" +
	"### Idempotent Behavior\n" +
	"- Install commands: Skip if already installed (exit code 0)\n" +
	"- Uninstall commands: Skip if not installed (exit code 0)\n" +
	"- Config initialization: Skip if config file exists (exit code 0)\n" +
	"- Daemon start: Skip if already running (exit code 0)\n" +
	"- Daemon stop: Skip if not running (exit code 0)\n" +
	"- Job cancellation: Skip if job not found or already completed (exit code 0)\n" +
	"\n" +
	"### Exit Code Behavior\n" +
	"- Idempotent no-ops always return exit code 0 (success)\n" +
	"- Non-zero exit codes only for actual failures\n" +
	"- Descriptive messages when operations are skipped\n" +
	"\n" +
	"### Benefits\n" +
	"- Safe to repeat commands without causing errors\n" +
	"- Ideal for automation and CI/CD pipelines\n" +
	"- Clear feedback when operations are skipped\n" +
